Good question Venky ğŸ‘Œ
Letâ€™s see **different alternative syntaxes for props in React** in a simple way.

---

# ğŸ”¹ 1ï¸âƒ£ Normal Props (Basic Way)

```jsx
function User(props) {
  return <h1>{props.name}</h1>;
}
```

Used like:

```jsx
<User name="Venky" />
```

---

# ğŸ”¹ 2ï¸âƒ£ Destructuring in Parameter (Most Common âœ…)

Instead of `props.name`, directly take it:

```jsx
function User({ name }) {
  return <h1>{name}</h1>;
}
```

ğŸ‘‰ Cleaner
ğŸ‘‰ Professional way
ğŸ‘‰ Mostly used in real projects

---

# ğŸ”¹ 3ï¸âƒ£ Destructuring Inside Function Body

Another way:

```jsx
function User(props) {
  const { name, age } = props;

  return (
    <>
      <h1>{name}</h1>
      <h2>{age}</h2>
    </>
  );
}
```

ğŸ‘‰ Same result
ğŸ‘‰ Just extracting manually

---

# ğŸ”¹ 4ï¸âƒ£ Default Props (If Value Not Passed)

### Method 1: Default value in parameter (Recommended)

```jsx
function User({ name = "Guest" }) {
  return <h1>{name}</h1>;
}
```

If used like:

```jsx
<User />
```

ğŸ‘‰ Output: **Guest**

---

### Method 2 (Older Way â€“ Not Recommended Now)

```jsx
User.defaultProps = {
  name: "Guest"
};
```

ğŸ‘‰ This works but modern React prefers parameter default.

---

# ğŸ”¹ 5ï¸âƒ£ Passing All Props (Spread Operator)

Sometimes you donâ€™t want to write each prop manually.

```jsx
const userData = {
  name: "Venky",
  age: 25
};

<User {...userData} />
```

Inside component:

```jsx
function User({ name, age }) {
  return (
    <>
      <h1>{name}</h1>
      <h2>{age}</h2>
    </>
  );
}
```

ğŸ‘‰ `{...userData}` spreads all properties as props.

---

# ğŸ”¹ 6ï¸âƒ£ Collect Remaining Props (Rest Operator)

If you want specific props + remaining:

```jsx
function User({ name, ...rest }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>{name}</h1>
      <p>{rest.age}</p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

ğŸ‘‰ `...rest` collects remaining props.

---

# ğŸ”¹ 7ï¸âƒ£ Passing Children as Props

Everything inside component tags becomes `props.children`.

```jsx
<User>
  <p>This is inside</p>
</User>
```

Component:

```jsx
function User({ children }) {
  return <div>{children}</div>;
}
```

ğŸ‘‰ `children` is also a prop.

---

# ğŸ”¥ Big Picture Summary

```text
props â†’ object
{ name } â†’ destructuring
name = "Guest" â†’ default value
{...obj} â†’ spread props
...rest â†’ collect remaining props
children â†’ special prop
```


